<p>&#8216;&#8221;Deeper pockets&#8221; is not sufficient justification for extending vicarious liability &#8220;beyond its principled boundaries&#8221; the Supreme Court has found, as it ruled a congregation cannot be liable for a rape committed by one of its elders.&#8217;</p>
